        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 4 at 9:33PM CDT until June 4 at 10:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 932 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles northwest
of Simms, or 23 miles southwest of Vega, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible. Hail
damage to vehicles is expected.

Locations impacted include...
Vega, Simms, and Adrian.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
